cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper deals with model reference adaptive control (MRAC) which is a subfield of control systems (cs.SY). The paper proposes a data-driven approach that uses past data to update controller parameters, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a finite-time system identifier, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper includes simulation results, which suggests that it may also fall under systems and control (cs.SD).
